<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-10-0267 </DOCNO><TEXT>The coolant level above the core is connected to the steam generator hotcollector via a suction pipe with a circulation pump. An overflow emptyingin the cold pipe via a plug is provided in the bottom part of the coldcollector. This connection allows cooling the core at a level of thecoolant below the mouths of the cold and hot reactor pipes without theneed of discharging fuel, i.e., during inspections and repairs of primarycoolant circuit valves. (J.B.). 1 fig.</TEXT></DOC>